Thailand Stocks: Bangkok Bank, Sri Trang, PTT Exploration

-- B y   B e r n i   M o e s t a f a
-- 
2011-04-12T05:42:12Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-12/thailand-stocks-bank-of-ayudhya-sri-trang-ptt-exploration.html
Shares of the following companies
had unusual moves in  Thailand  trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of 12:30 p.m. break in Bangkok.  The SET Index declined 6.71 points, or 0.6 percent, to
1,069.62.  Banks: Bangkok Bank Pcl (BBL TB), Thailand’s biggest by
assets, fell 2.2 percent to 177.5 baht, poised for its biggest
loss since March 31.  Kasikornbank Pcl (KBANK)  , the third
largest, fell 1.5 percent to 127.5 baht.  Bank of Ayudhya Pcl (BAY) 
, the fifth largest, dropped 2 percent to 25 baht.  Thai inflation will accelerate in the second half of this
year, central bank Governor Prasarn Trairatvorakul said today.
Faster inflation adds pressure on the central bank to further
raise borrowing costs.  Energy companies:  PTT Pcl (PTT)  , Thailand’s biggest
energy company, slid 1.1 percent to 364 baht.  PTT Exploration &
Production Pcl (PTTEP)  , the nation’s only publicly traded oil
explorer, lost 2.3 percent to 188.5 baht.  Crude oil for May delivery declined 2.5 percent to $109.92
a barrel in New York yesterday, the sharpest drop since March 15.
The contract fell 1.3 percent to $108.47 in after-hours trading.  Sri Trang Agro-Industry Pcl (STA)  , Thailand’s biggest
publicly traded rubber producer, dropped 2.3 percent to 32.25
baht. Rubber declined from a five-week high, with the September-
delivery contract plunging as much as 3.8 percent to 457.2 yen
per kilogram ($5,688 a metric ton) in  Tokyo .  To contact the reporter on this story:
Berni Moestafa in Jakarta at 
 bmoestafa@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Reinie Booysen at   rbooysen@bloomberg.net . 